    "faqMetaTitle": "Growth OS FAQ — 10 AI agents for pool pros",
    "faqMetaDescription": "All the answers about Growth OS: the 10 agents, the pipeline, the marketplace, commission, GDPR compliance.",
    "faqEyebrow": "Growth OS FAQ",
    "faqTitle": "Frequently asked questions about AQWELIA Growth OS",
    "faqSubtitle": "Everything you need to know about the 10 AI agents, the pipeline, the marketplace and commission.",
    "faqQ1": "What is Growth OS?",
    "faqA1": "Growth OS is a growth engine for pool pros made of 10 specialized AI agents. Each agent has a precise scope (capture, qualification, diagnostic, matching, appointment, nurturing, quote, attribution, compliance) and works 24/7 to turn your leads into customers.",
    "faqQ2": "How many agents does Growth OS have?",
    "faqA2": "10 agents: Offer Builder, Lead Capture, Qualification, Pre-diagnostic, Matching, Appointment Setter, Nurturing, Quote, Attribution and Compliance Supervisor. Each has an objective, tools, a budget and a maximum number of actions.",
    "faqQ3": "How does commission work?",
    "faqA3": "You only pay the commission if the lead results in a billed intervention. The rate depends on your plan (10% in Starter, 8% in Pro, 6% in Performance). The commission is clamped between €25 (minimum) and €150 (maximum) per won lead.",
    "faqQ4": "Do the agents respect GDPR?",
    "faqA4": "Yes. The Compliance Supervisor agent verifies consent before every sensitive action. The consent must be present and less than 24 months old. Non-EU transfers require Standard Contractual Clauses (SCC).",
    "faqQ5": "Can I use my own email templates?",
    "faqA5": "Yes. The Nurturing agent uses default templates (cold_intro, warm_recall, winback_we_miss_you, etc.) but you can customize them in the organization settings.",
    "faqQ6": "How are leads captured?",
    "faqA6": "Seven sources: website, widget, B2C marketplace (AQWELIA consumers), QR codes, ad campaigns, partners and referrals. Each source is tracked by the Attribution agent.",
    "faqQ7": "How long does it take to set up Growth OS?",
    "faqA7": "Less than 5 minutes. You create your organization, plug in your sources (widget, QR codes) and the agents start capturing. Email templates and the quote catalog are ready out of the box.",
    "faqQ8": "Does Growth OS work with my existing CRM?",
    "faqA8": "The Performance plan includes an integration API (REST) to sync leads, appointments and quotes with your CRM or ERP. Starter and Pro plans use the built-in dashboard.",
    "faqQ9": "What happens if an agent fails?",
    "faqA9": "The agent logs its status (failed or escalated) in AgentRun. If the confidence score is low or a required action is unavailable, the agent escalates to a human (manual_dispatcher, manual_scheduler, dpo, etc.).",
    "faqQ10": "Do my leads' data belong to me?",
    "faqA10": "Yes. You remain the sole owner of your leads' data. We never resell any data. GDPR exports and deletions are available on request.",
    "faqQ11": "Is Growth OS available outside France?",
    "faqA11": "Yes. Growth OS is available in all EU countries. The Compliance Supervisor handles non-EU transfers via Standard Contractual Clauses (SCC) where applicable.",
    "faqQ12": "How do I cancel my subscription?",
    "faqA12": "From the dashboard, Settings tab > Subscription > Cancel. The cancellation takes effect at the end of the current billing cycle. No commitment, no penalty.",
